---
import Prose from '../../layouts/Prose.astro';
import FlashcardDrill from '../../components/course/FlashcardDrill.astro';
import { TOOLS } from '../../lib/tools';

const tool = TOOLS.find((t) => t.slug === 'flashcards')!;
---

<Prose
  title={tool.title}
  description={tool.description}
  crumbs={[{ name: 'Tools', href: '/tools/' }, { name: tool.title }]}
  kicker="Practice Tools"
>
  <p>
    Everything in geomancy is built from sixteen figures, and judgment begins where recognition
    ends: a chart cannot be read while its figures still have to be deciphered. These drills
    train recognition in layers. First the figure to its name, then the name to its meaning:
    translation, planet and the core significations. Last, the figure to each of its
    attributions on its own: planet, sign, quality and element. The course's standard, set in
    <a href="/course/the-alphabet-of-the-earth/">Lesson 2</a> and
    <a href="/course/the-sixteen-natures/">Lesson 3</a>, is two clean passes in a row before
    moving on; score is kept for the round only, so every visit starts fresh.
  </p>
  <p>
    The full reference for each figure (dots, names, attributions in every source's system, and
    the placement columns) is at <a href="/figures/">the sixteen figures</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>Figure to name</h2>
  <FlashcardDrill />

  <h2>Name to meaning</h2>
  <FlashcardDrill mode="meaning" />

  <h2>Figure to planet</h2>
  <FlashcardDrill mode="figure-planet" />

  <h2>Figure to sign</h2>
  <FlashcardDrill mode="figure-sign" />

  <h2>Figure to quality</h2>
  <FlashcardDrill mode="figure-quality" />

  <h2>Figure to element</h2>
  <FlashcardDrill mode="figure-element" />
</Prose>
